Plateau State Commissioner for Environment, Usman Bamaiyi’s wife and daughter kidnapped about 11 days ago have regained their freedom from the hands of their abductors. DAILY POST recalls that Usman Bamaiyi, the Plateau State Commissioner for Environment’s wife and daughter were abducted when terrorists stormed the Commissioner’s residence located in Gindiri community, Mangu Local Government Area of the State in the early hours of Saturday, 9th April, 2022. A source in Gindiri community told DAILY POST that they have been released to the family. According to the source, “The two kidnapped victims regained their freedom on Monday night.” The wife and the daughter of the Commissioner were abducted in Gindiri, their residence in the early hours of Saturday, April 9, 2022.